  "response": "The chemical formula for zinc is Zn.\n\nThis is determined by:\n1. Zinc is a pure metallic element, so it is represented by its chemical symbol (Zn)\n2. In its elemental state, zinc exists as individual zinc atoms\n3. The symbol Zn comes from its name (derived from the German word \"zink\")\n4. Its atomic number is 30, which means it has 30 protons in its nucleus\n5. In most chemical compounds, zinc typically forms a +2 ion (Zn2+)\n\nThe chemical symbol is standardized by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC) and represents the simplest representation of the element in its pure, uncombined state.",
